8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
9 Section 1. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 72-5133a is hereby amended to read
10 as follows: 72-5133a. (a) On August 15, 2024, and each August 15
11 thereafter, the director of the budget, in consultation with the director
12 of property valuation, shall certify to the director of accounts and
13 reports if the:
14 (1) Exemption provided by K.S.A. 79-201x, and amendments
15 thereto, is increased from $42,049 for any tax year; or
16 (2) rate of ad valorem tax levied by a school district pursuant to
17 K.S.A. 72-5142, and amendments thereto, is decreased from 20 mills.
18 (b) (1) The director of the budget shall certify to the director of
19 accounts and reports and shall transfer a copy of such certification to
20 the director of legislative research the amount of revenue that the:
21 (A) Increase in the exemption provided by K.S.A. 79-201x, and
22 amendments thereto, would have generated for the tax year if the
23 exemption amount was $42,049; and
24 (B) decrease in the rate of ad valorem tax levied by a school district
25 pursuant to K.S.A. 72-5142, and amendments thereto, would have
26 generated for the tax year if the tax rate levied would have been 20 mills.
27 (2) Upon receipt of such certification, or as soon thereafter as
28 moneys are available, the director of accounts and reports shall
29 transfer such certified amount from the state general fund to the state
30 school district finance fund of the department of education.
